THE PLINY FISK. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 6, 1917.) No. 236. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Carpenter & Park, now Park & Mattison, of New York City (Samuel Park, of New York City, of counsel), for The Pliny Fisk. Macklin, Brown & Purdy, of New York City (Pierre M. Brown and Frank J. Whitcomb, both of New York City, of counsel), for claimants.

Before COXE, WARD, and ROGERS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
